WaterFall Braid

A waterfall braid is a beautiful and intricate hairstyle that combines braiding with flowing, loose sections of hair to create the appearance of cascading waterfalls. The key feature of the waterfall braid is its unique method of weaving, where portions of the hair are dropped as the braid progresses, allowing the remaining hair to cascade freely.
00:07

Two Ears Braid

The "two ears braid" is a fun and playful hairstyle that often involves creating two distinct braids that resemble the shape of "ears" on either side of the head.
00:12

Fulanie Braid

Fulani braids are a traditional and stylish hairstyle originating from the Fulani people of West Africa, particularly the Fula or Fulani ethnic group. The look has become popular worldwide due to its distinct, intricate design and versatility. Fulani braids typically feature a combination of cornrows, individual braids, and accessories, making it a bold yet elegant style.
